  sugar: 2 g
  protein: 28 g
servings: 2
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees and cut the @cherry tomatoes{1} in half. Remove
the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and @red pepper{1} and then slice into strips.
Lay out on a #baking tray{} then drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with a pinch
of @salt{}. Roast in your oven for ~{15-20%mins} until starting to brown at the edges.

Boil a #pot{} of water with a pinch of @salt{}. Peel and finely chop the @onion{1/2}(peeled and finely chopped) and @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and finely chopped). Roughly chop the @basil{1/2%small bunch}(roughly chopped).

Cook the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} in the boiling water for ~{11%mins} or until 'al dente'.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness
> left in the middle - taste it as you go to get it just right.

Add a splash of @olive oil{} to a #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once warm, add the
@chorizo{1}(diced) and onion and cook gently for ~{5%mins} until soft. Add your
garlic and a few good grinds of @black pepper{} and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Cut the @black olives{2} in half lengthways and add to the pan along with a splash
of the pasta water.

> Adding pasta water is a classic Italian trick and adds some salt and starchiness
> to give you a bit of a sauce.

When your pasta is cooked, it's time to combine everything. Add your roasted tomatoes
and pepper to the frying pan and tear in half the @mozzarella{1}(torn in half) and
most, but not all, of your chopped basil. Add your drained pasta and toss everything
together.

Serve with your remaining mozzarella torn over the top, the rest of your basil and
a drizzle of @olive oil{}.